<xref keyref="SAFEUSE" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-90C8F720-CF47-4BFD-B0A4-AF5208D41820.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Instructions for safe use (Technician)?>Instructions for safe use (Technician)</xref> 
</p></note><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></li><li id="LI_14F2360B54394026972652B71009438A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the chiller unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="06DISA003" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?></xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the Embedded controller box. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="21DISA017" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-AC2E7AD7-DFD5-44D2-8411-A86E0560D001.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21 How to remove the Embedded controller box?>21 How to remove the Embedded controller box</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_5232B115C44C4A13A0F0FA8D704DDD74" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_9BF138AF80F34359907B618BBA28D88F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Small screwdriver 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li><li id="LI_88A0F8686D4746559B1B7977EA80969C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T10. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-B00F5E58-2D5E-4E0D-AF17-7AE33CD5861D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-70ED4C92-6E61-4453-ABB2-B27D25F51908-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-70ED4C92-6E61-4453-ABB2-B27D25F51908-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_ADE51AAC180E4895A425E9129C2696CB" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove </title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_E9061EA725864628BF4B2DB22FA106BB" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Unlock the clip of the CMOS battery and remove the CMOS battery. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-54D644B4-C1D0-4604-BE70-8C8D190DDF09" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-82A52F2B-5685-4D34-8807-4691430F6B74-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-82A52F2B-5685-4D34-8807-4691430F6B74-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_F77204E29D3E4F6D8F3503958683C72F" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p><note id="GUID-C4ADB851-3A92-43E6-9298-F10E9184D20A" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> In case the controller does not start when power is applied, create a short between the pin 1 and pin 2 of the connector 3. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-ECFBC9EF-E01C-4CD0-9FF5-6E4EC82451AD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FED859BA-1F5A-4B57-B282-B0E96CE09750-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FED859BA-1F5A-4B57-B282-B0E96CE09750-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Component 3, Control interface connector - functions: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PIN 1</b> - ATX Power on/off button connect 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PIN 2</b> - ATX Power on/off button connect 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PIN 3</b> - Status control detect positive 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PIN 4</b> - Status control detect negative 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">After starting up check if the time and time zone on the engine are correct. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">On the print UI the date and time can be checked and changed via the menu: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> System -&gt; Regional Settings 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In the SettingEditor the date and time can be checked via: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Preferences -&gt; System settings -&gt; Date and time 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-6C63EF43-7F31-48D5-A8F0-5338D21560E2.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
